Rice paper dumplings | Recipe ⬇️ (Deutsch in den kommentaren)

In a large pan sauté
-2 spring onions, chopped
-2 carrots, shredded
-1/4 white cabbage, shredded
-7 oz mushrooms
-1 tbsp ginger, grated
-1 block tofu (7oz)
In some oil for a few mins until the veggies start to soften, then add
-2 tbsp soy sauce
-1 tbsp rice vinegar 
1 tbsp corn starch
Stir and set aside.
In the meantime, prepare the dipping sauce.
To a heat proof bowl add
-2 tbsp chili flakes
-1 tbsp Sichuan pepper
-1 tbsp sesame seeds
-1 garlic clove, minced
-2 tbsp spring onion, chopped
Pour hot oil on it and then add
-2 tbsp soy sauce
-1 tbsp rice vinegar 
To prepare the dumplings, dip a rice paper in warm water for a few secs and then place on a damp surface to fill and fold them.
Add the dumpling on another rice paper sheet and fold again. Pan fry the dumplings on each side until golden brown and enjoy :)

Stuffed Flatbread

To make the dough, mix
-2,5 cups flour
-1 cup water
-1/2 tsp salt
-2 tbsp olive oil
and kneed until you have a soft dough. Cover and set aside for 30 min.
In the meantime, boil 
-3 medium sized potatoes 
and mash them. Add 
-1 tbsp olive oil or vegan butter
And season with
-salt & pepper, to taste
Cut the dough into equal portions, roll it out 
and fill with the mashed potatoes,
-vegan pesto of choice
-shredded vegan cheese 
Close the dough and cook both sides in a pan on medium heat until golden
Brush with a little 
-olive oil or melted butter mixed with fresh herbs of choice
Serve hot and enjoy :)

You NEED to try these 🥞Vegan Protein Banana Pancake Bites🥞 

With 27g Protein per serving 😱😍🙌🏼

For the pancakes:
- 4 scoops (100g) @Bulk Vegan Protein Pancake Mix
- 100ml water
- 2 ripe bananas
- 1-2 tbsp Bulk coconut oil (for frying)

For the peanut butter sauce:
- 3 tbsp Bulk powdered peanut butter
- 2.5 tbsp milk of choice 
- 2 tsp Bulk maple syrup zero calorie syrup™

Method:
- Mix the pancake mix and water to a smooth, thin batter. 
- Slice the banana into thin discs, then dip into the batter to coat. 
- Heat the coconut oil in a large frying pan over a medium heat. Fry each banana bite for a minute on each side or until golden brown.
- Mix the ingredients for the peanut butter sauce. Drizzle over the pancake bites and tuck in.

Serves 2. Per serving: 473 Kcals | 27g Protein | 55g Carbs | 17g Fat

juice of 1 lime
1 knob of fresh ginger, grated or finely minced

1 tbsp sesame oil

1 cup hot water

The best, creamiest sweet potato hummus—and the best darn savory snack. I’ve been making this one for years, and it’s still my favorite hummus for fall! 🍁🍠
〰️
1 medium-sized sweet potato
1 1/2 cups cooked chickpeas (1 14.5-oz can, drained and rinsed)
¼ cup tahini
2 tablespoons freshly squeezed lemon juice
1 clove garlic
3/4 teaspoon fine salt
1/4 teaspoon sweet or smoked ground paprika
1/3 cup water
〰️
1️⃣ Roast, steam, or microwave your sweet potato till fork tender (I prick mine with a fork and microwave on high for 6-10 min, or until it’s totally cooked). After steaming or scooping the flesh out of the skin (if roasting or microwaving), you should have about 200g cooked sweet potato.
2️⃣ Place all ingredients except for the water in a food processor fitted with the S blade. Pulse a few times to break the chickpeas down.
3️⃣ Run the motor of the food processor and drizzle the water in in a thin stream. Continue processing for 2-3 minutes, or until the hummus is very creamy. Stop once or twice to scrape down the sides of the food processor bowl. If the hummus is too thick for your liking, add a tablespoon or two of water and continue processing. Enjoy!

Crunchy Caramel Cups 🍫

I have not stopped snacking on these! They are so tasty and the texture is so good 👌🏼 who wants to try them?

Makes approx 12

Base:
▪️120g oat flour (1 cup) 
▫️25g cup cocoa powder (1/4 cup) 
▪️50g cup maple syrup (1/4 cup) 
▫️25g coconut oil (1 tbsp) 

Filling:
▪️100g cup caramel sauce (1/2 cup)
▫️40g cup walnuts (1/4 cup) 

Top:
▪️35g dairy free dark chocolate (1/4 cup)
▫️25g coconut oil (1 tbsp) 

1️⃣ In a large bowl combine oat flour with cocoa powder, maple syrup and coconut oil. Mix together until sticky (add a tiny bit of water if needed)
2️⃣ Press mixture into a mini muffin pan. I used a silicone one. 
3️⃣ Spoon in the caramel and add chopped walnuts. 
4️⃣ Combine the dark chocolate with coconut oil and microwave for approx 30 seconds until chocolate has melted. Stir together and pour over each cup.
5️⃣ Set in the freezer for 1 hour. Gently remove cups from muffin pan and store in a container in the fridge for up to 5 days.

Air fryer apple fries 💫

These are such a fun sweet snack to make. 

INGREDIENTS

2 apples – cored and cut into “fries”
¼ cup arrowroot starch or cornstarch
¼ cup coconut sugar or brown sugar
½ tbsp cinnamon
2 tsp liquid oil of choice

INSTRUCTIONS

Add apples to a bowl. Toss with starch, sugar, cinnamon and oil until every slice is mostly coated. Depending on the size of your apples you may have some of the coating left.
Add apples to your air fryer in an even layer. Air fry at 400 degrees for 10-12 minutes (shaking halfway through) until apples are browned and slightly crisped. They will still be soft and not as crisp as actual fries.
Serve and enjoy. These fries go great with my vegan fruit dip.

𝗖𝗥𝗘𝗔𝗠𝗬 𝗩𝗘𝗚𝗘𝗧𝗔𝗕𝗟𝗘 𝗚𝗡𝗢𝗖𝗖𝗛𝗜 𝗦𝗢𝗨𝗣

𝗜𝗻𝗴𝗿𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀

1 (17 oz) package of Vegan Gnocchi  2 medium Carrots sliced 2 ribs of Celery chopped 1 small Onion chopped 4 cloves of Garlic minced 1 1/2 cups (120 g) of Broccoli (if using frozen then let thaw) roughly chopped 2 cups (60 g) Spinach packed and then roughly chopped 3 1/2 Tbsp (52 g)  Vegan Butter 3 1/2 Tbsp (52 g) Flour 3 cups (709 ml) Vegetable Broth 2 1/2 cups (591 ml) of Plant Milk  1 1/2 tsp (7.5 g)Thyme 1/2 tsp (2.5 g) Onion Salt 1/8 tsp Nutmeg Pinch of Red Chili Flakes (optional) Salt & Pepper to taste 

𝗗𝗶𝗿𝗲𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝘀

1. Heat the oil on med heat and sauté the onions, celery and carrots until onions become translucent. About 3-5 minutes.

2. Add in the broccoli, thyme, garlic, onion salt and chili flakes (if using) then continue cooking or another couple of minutes or until the garlic is fragrant. 

3. Add in the butter and once melted add in the flour. Mix well and stir occasionally while you cook for another minute to cook out the raw flour flavor. 

4. Add in the vegetable broth and milk and bring to a soft boil. Lower the heat to med low and simmer for 8 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste. 

5. Add in the gnocchi, nutmeg  and chopped spinach and cook for 5-8 minutes or until the gnocchi is cooked through and the spinach is wilted. Check for seasoning and adjust with salt and pepper.
